OL,6,F"Having identified their
OL,7,Fvulnerabilities and earned their trust
OL,8,FHarris contrived to siphon off their
OL,9,Fassets, netting what remained
OL,10,Ffollowing their deaths, despite
OL,11,Fsafeguarding measures which should
OL,12,Fhave protected them."
OL,14,FDC Woodall added: "His endeavours to
OL,15,Favoid justice saw no hesitation on Mr
OL,16,FHarris's part to publicly insult the
OL,17,Fvictims' families and allow another
OL,18,Fvulnerable person to face the
OL,19,Fpossibility of conviction for his
OL,20,Funwitting part in Mr. Harris's
OL,21,Fdeception.
